2052.subject: ASAP
2052.descrlong: Provides supplemental support for senior capstone course(s). Students work in small groups with a tutor from the Academic Skills Achievement Program (ASAP), and receive assistance on writing and editing their capstone projects. Groups meet for 50 to 90 minutes per week. Must be taken concurrently with a Capstone 400 course. Credit/no credit only. (Offered every semester.)

2054.subject: ASAP
2054.descrlong: Provides supplemental support for Senior Capstone courses. Students work in small groups with a tutor from the Academic Skills Achievement Program (ASAP), and receive assistance on parts of the writing process including: organizing research, finding a topic, formulating a thesis, developing content, and learning to proofread. Groups meet for 50 to 90 minutes per week. Must be taken concurrently with a Capstone 400 course. Credit/no credit only. (Offered every semester.)
